## 1. Accounting policy

Heritage assets are recognised and measured in accordance with the South African Standard of Generally Recognised Accounting Practice on Heritage Assets (GRAP 103).

Heritage assets are recognised when:

- the asset meets the definition of a heritage asset; and
- the cost or fair value at the date of acquisition can be measured reliably.

Heritage assets are not depreciated, on the basis that they have indefinite useful lives and that their values typically do not diminish over time. Each heritage asset is reviewed annually for impairment in terms of GRAP 21 / GRAP 26.

