Revaluation surpluses are credited to the revaluation reserve in net assets (OCI). Decreases first reduce any surplus accumulated for the same asset in the reserve, with the balance recognised in surplus or deficit (GRAP 103.51).

## 5. Impairment

The entity reviews heritage assets for indicators of impairment annually. Where an asset's recoverable amount is less than its carrying amount, the difference is recognised as an impairment loss against the revaluation reserve for that asset to the extent available, with the residual recognised in surplus or deficit (GRAP 103.62 read with GRAP 21 / GRAP 26).

